Note:
Runa Standard Library: AI Agent Memory - Procedural Memory System
Production-ready procedural memory framework for storing, organizing, and executing
learned skills, routines, and action sequences with optimization and adaptation.

Advanced features include:
- Hierarchical skill decomposition with sub-routine management
- Skill learning and refinement through practice and feedback
- Procedure execution with error recovery and adaptation
- Skill transfer and generalization across contexts
- Performance monitoring and optimization algorithms
- Conditional execution with context-aware branching
- Skill composition for complex behavior assembly
- Automatic routine discovery and chunking
- Expertise development with proficiency tracking
- Multi-modal skill representation supporting various action types
:End Note

Type called "SkillPrimitive":
    primitive_id as String
    name as String
    description as String
    action_type as String
    parameters as Dictionary[String, Any]
    preconditions as List[Dictionary]
    postconditions as List[Dictionary]
    execution_time as Float
    success_rate as Float
    error_patterns as List[Dictionary]
    optimization_level as Integer
    practice_count as Integer
    last_executed as Float

Type called "ProceduralSkill":
    skill_id as String
    skill_name as String
    skill_type as String
    complexity_level as Integer
    skill_primitives as List[String]
    execution_sequence as List[Dictionary]
    branching_conditions as List[Dictionary]
    error_handling as List[Dictionary]
    performance_metrics as Dictionary[String, Float]
    proficiency_level as Float
    acquisition_time as Float
    practice_sessions as Integer
    success_history as List[Boolean]
    context_dependencies as List[String]
    skill_variants as List[String]

